column1: #Text=Plympton is a small town in Massachusetts on the South Shore .

#Text=Later , the leg became infected and she was hospitalized . Her gender was discovered and she was honorably discharged .
#Text=It is so small that many people fear blinking as they are driving down route 58 because they might miss the town .

#Text=Deborah Sampson , a woman who dressed as a man and fought in the Revolutionary War , was born in Plympton , but the only other exciting news to come from the town is the addition of their first traffic light in 2008 .
#Text=Overall , Plympton is a great place to raise a family because of their schooling ( Silver Lake School District ) and the small population .
#Text=The new route 44 is the best way in from the highway .
#Text=Get off at the Plympton-Carver-58 exit ( exits are not numbered ) and bear right off the exit and continue north on 58 to reach Plympton .
#Text=There is a small , regional airport in Plymouth called Plymouth Municipal Airport ( 246 South Meadow Road , 508-746-8003 ) .
#Text=Travellers usually prefer Logan Airport in Boston or T.F. Greene Airport in Warwick , RI .
#Text=Plympton is so small that there is no public transportation .
#Text=There are few sidewalks so walking is not advised .
